  "text": "Our experiments have shown the value of shape descriptors for matching specific objects, but shape has also been widely recognised as being particularly important for characterising object classes. Therefore, an important area for future work will be to test our features in the context of generic object class recognition. We also intend to test the performance of our features for matching objects to large databases, in which case our pair matching method may be expected to further increase in importance. Another area we intend to examine in future research is to exploit the Maximally Stable Colour Region extension of MSER [CITATION_1] for improving the identification of stable regions.",
